His mind was completely gentle toward every living being in the three levels of the cosmos
He didn't exalt or demean any of them at all
'Sabbe satta'  'May all living beings who are fellows in suffering birth aging illness and death'  'avera hontu'  'be free from enmity' all the way to 'sukhi attanam pariharantu'  'may they maintain themselves with ease' That was his benevolence
He gave equality to all living beings
He didn't lean because his mind didn't have anything to lean
