After giving up its desires the mind was no longer involved with the past
It stayed in the circle of the present and would do nothing but repeat or meditate on 'buddho' Whether or not it would get any results would depend on what 'buddho' would grant
Finally the mind became still and 'buddho' was no longer necessary so I could let go of the meditation word at that moment  and at that point the mind was willing to settle down
Before it hadn't been willing
When the mind had settled down in stillness there was no need to repeat the word 'buddho' All that remained was simple awareness  clear and conspicuous  so the mind stayed with that simple awareness
As soon as it withdrew I would start pumping 'buddho' back in
